## H-Claude Framework

```yaml
# Architecture: Orchestrator + HD (see $SSOT/HD_INTERFACE.md)
architecture:
  orchestrator: Development engine (Python TDD loop) - ROOT/orchestrator/
  hd: PO/User-Proxy - manages Orchestrator on user's behalf (.claude/skills/)

# SSoT (Single Source of Truth)
ssot:
  northstar: .claude/PM/SSoT/NORTHSTAR.md    # Vision, goals, constraints
  roadmap: .claude/PM/SSoT/ROADMAP.yaml      # Phases, dependencies
  changelog: .claude/PM/CHANGELOG.md          # Work history
  context: .claude/context.yaml               # Session state
  adrs: .claude/PM/SSoT/ADRs/                 # Decision records

# Shortcuts
paths:
  $PM: .claude/PM
  $SSOT: $PM/SSoT
  $NORTH: $SSOT/NORTHSTAR.md
  $ROAD: $SSOT/ROADMAP.yaml
  $TEMP: $PM/TEMP
  $LIB: .claude/lib

# Commands
commands:
  /think-tank --roadmap: Create development phases from NORTHSTAR
  /think-tank --phase=X: Plan specific phase execution
  /think-tank "topic": Ad-hoc research/decision session
  /hc-glass: Code/system review
  /red-team: Deep investigation audit
  /ask <file>: Get Pro agent feedback on document

# HD Skills (requirements extraction)
skills:
  /genesis: Bootstrap - detect project state, start interview
  /diamond-diverge: Explore problem space (Why, What, Edges)
  /diamond-converge: Prioritize entities (MoSCoW grouping)
  /diamond-synthesize: Lock decisions, create artifacts
  /draft-userstory: Generate UserStory from requirements
  /draft-adr: Generate ADR from decisions

# Workflow
workflow:
  1_requirements: HD interview → UserStories in $NORTH
  2_roadmap: /think-tank --roadmap → $ROAD
  3_plan: /think-tank --phase=X → execution-plan.yaml
  4_execute: Orchestrator → Implementation
  5_review: /hc-glass → Quality check
  6_commit: Git commit → CHANGELOG update

# HD Role: PO/User-Proxy
hd_role:
  dialogue_loop: User-facing conversation (separate from Workflow Loop)
  can: Interview, clarify, lock ADRs, approve/reject stories, update state
  cannot: Edit code directly - MUST use Orchestrator process
  produces: NORTHSTAR, User Stories, ADRs, Logic Trees

# HD Interview Flow
hd_flow: /genesis → /diamond-diverge → /diamond-converge → /diamond-synthesize → /draft-userstory

# Session Protocol
session:
  start:
    - Read context.yaml for current focus
    - Check ROADMAP for active phase
  during:
    - Update context.yaml after significant work
    - Delegate to sub-agents to preserve context
    - Use $TEMP for drafts and scratch work
  end:
    - Update CHANGELOG
    - Commit with descriptive message

# Rules
rules:
  - SSoT First: Read NORTHSTAR before major decisions
  - No Assumptions: Ask for clarification when unclear
  - Fix Dont Workaround: Address root causes
  - Context is Precious: Delegate to preserve main context
  - Document Decisions: ADRs for architectural choices
  - Changelog is Worklog: Update after every commit
```

